	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_ERAPTOR">
			<Text>Raptor</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_ERAPTOR_HELP">
			<Text>Raptors are powerful anti-armor vehicles that can also perform interceptions (Note: the intercept chance in only 50% and the range is 2 tiles) and can carry one plane. They require 2 aluminum and 1 oil and can't capture cities.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_ERAPTOR_TEXT">
			<Text>During the Great War, cloudships were built using unicorn magic and piloted by pegasi in battle. As a result, the Enclave has been unable to build any more cloudships after the Megaspells fell. [NEWLINE][NEWLINE] Raptors class cloudships are built for small scale assault on ground forces and ideally built for aerial combat. They are fast and highly maneuverable cloudships and were notably used to take down attacking forces, like dragons. They are very susceptible to Sonic Rainboom attacks which annihilate the clouds giving them lift, causing them to crash. (Text taken from Fo:E wiki)</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_ERAPTOR_STRATEGY">
			<Text>Raptor Cloudships are land units that can traverse the sea without embarking and can carry 1 air unit. This ability allows them to bring aircraft quickly to the battlefield. They can also double as an anti-armor and anti-air unit, as the Raptor recieves a bonus vs armor and aircraft. However, Raptors are suseptible to Anti-air units and can't capture cities.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_GPERAPTOR">
			<Text>Energy Beam Weaponry</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_PROMOTION_GPERAPTOR_HELP">
			<Text>A Raptor's use of Armor-piercing Energy Beam weapons allow it to hit air and surface targets. This makes the Raptor capable of intercepting aircraft and grants a combat bonus versus armor units.</Text>
		</Row>
